    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Horrendous Job</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Elizabeth Dearstyne letter on Richard Sandomir's Feb 13 article on television coverage of Winter Olympics; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>Thank you Richard Sandomir (''Breaking News, Just 23 Hours Later,'' The Times, Feb. 13) for expressing what I hope are the sentiments of all of us who eagerly await the Olympics every four years. We watch to enjoy seeing the very best of the world's athletes compete, regardless of their countries of origin. For these Olympics, with time differences fully understood, CBS has done one horrendous job by presenting disjointed events, mediocre commentary, accident rerun overload and very lackluster leadership by Jim Nantz. Need I mention the ads?</p>
        <p>ELIZABETH DEARSTYNE  Madison, N.J.</p>
      </block>
